Become a Part of the NIKE, Inc. Team

NIKE, Inc. does more than outfit the world's best athletes. It is a place to explore potential, obliterate boundaries and push out the edges of what can be. The company looks for people who can grow, think, dream and create. Its culture thrives by embracing diversity and rewarding imagination. The brand seeks achievers, leaders and visionaries. At NIKE, Inc. it's about each person bringing skills and passion to a challenging and constantly evolving game.

Lead Machine Learning Engineer-NIKE, Inc., San Francisco, CA. Develop and program integrated software algorithms to structure, analyze and leverage data in product and systems applications in both structured and unstructured environments. Develop and communicate descriptive, diagnostic, predictive and prescriptive insights/algorithms. Use machine language and statistical modeling techniques such as decision trees, logistic regression, Bayesian analysis and others. Develop and evaluate algorithms to improve product system performance, quality, data management and accuracy. Use current programming language, technologies to translate algorithms and technical specifications into code. Complete programming and implement efficiencies, perform testing and debugging. Complete documentation and procedures for installation and maintenance. Apply deep learning technologies to give computers the capability to visualize, learn and respond to complex situations. Adapt machine learning to areas such as virtual reality, augmented reality, artificial intelligence, robotics and other products that allow users to have an interactive experience. Work with large scale computing frameworks, data analysis systems and modeling environments. Telecommuting is available from anywhere in the U.S., except from AK, AL, AR, DE, HI, IA, ID, IN, KS, KY, LA, MT, ND, NE, NH, NM, NV, OH, OK, RI, SD, VT, WV, and WY.

Employer will accept a Master's Degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Computer Information Systems, or Engineering and 2 years of experience OR a Ph.D. in Computer Science, Statistics, Computer Information Systems, or Engineering and completion of a Ph.D-level course, research project, internship, or thesis or one year of experience in the job offered or engineering-related occupation.
Python, Spark, Java, Scala;
AI/ML techniques, including neural networks, tree ensembles, regressions, and hypothesis testing;
Data and Machine learning pipelines using Scikit-learn, Tensorflow, Spark ML (MLlib), Open CV;
SQL, and data query languages;
Architecting or delivering cloud solutions such, as Google cloud or AWS or similar platforms;
Algorithms, such as ALS, Neural Nets, CNN, Clustering, personalization techniques, time series, NLP and image modeling;
End-to-end lifecycle of machine learning systems or Machine learning engineering development;
Delivering and supporting high impact solutions that scale across very large datasets to production;
Track recording of delivering and supporting high impact solutions that scale across very large datasets to production;
Lead and mentor team members;
Partnering across product, architecture and engineering
Lifecycle of model development from experimentation to production and measurement.

Rate of Pay: $183800 to $262037.30 per Year

#LI-DNI

NIKE, Inc. is a growth company that looks for team members to grow with it. Nike offers a generous total rewards package, casual work environment, a diverse and inclusive culture, and an electric atmosphere for professional development. No matter the location, or the role, every Nike employee shares one galvanizing mission: To bring inspiration and innovation to every athlete* in the world.

NIKE, Inc. is committed to employing a diverse workforce. Qualified applicants will receive consideration without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, veteran status, or disability.

Benefits

Whether it's transportation or financial health, we continually invest in our employees to help them achieve greatness - inside and outside of work. All who work here should be able to realize their full potential.

Playrix is the largest gaming company in Eastern Europe. We are one of the top 3 most successful mobile game publishers in the world. Our projects — the Scapes™ series, Manor Matters, Fishdom, and Township — are played by over 130 million people every month.
We're looking for a talented ML Engineer who will strengthen our team.

This role requires relocation from Russia and Belarus to one of our offices or remote work from other countries (except Russia and Belarus).

Tasks
Development of services based on machine learning algorithms in such areas as:
Offer recommendations and pricing;
Dynamic difficulty adjustments;
Bots for playtesting and level difficulty evaluation;
LTV forecasting;
Marketing campaign automation;
Response prediction, uplift modeling;
Develop and support machine learning models and data preparation pipelines, deploying and supporting MLOps infrastructure;
Working with product teams and game developers, supporting the implementation of machine learning-based tools.
Requirements
5+years of experience developing services based on machine learning;
Excellent Python and basic C++ programming skills;
Strong mathematical background: understanding of probability theory, applied statistics, and machine learning;
Thorough knowledge of SQL and databases;
Fluency in Russian and proficiency in written English.

What we expect from you
Love for writing beautiful code that is easy to maintain;
Desire to create reliable services that require minimal support;
Business orientation, ability to find an applied solution in a limited time without adding unnecessary complexity;
Proactive attitude, ability to take responsibility for results, ability to act in a situation of uncertainty.

Our Perks
Flexibility
Work from wherever you like (your home, one of our many offices, or a hybrid combination) and whenever you like thanks to our flexible work schedule.
Healthcare
We reimburse online sessions with a psychologist and offer you and your children healthcare, including dental insurance and treatment for COVID-19.
Work-life balance
We offer a generous amount of paid vacation days and sick leave. In special circumstances, additional days off can be requested.
Professional development and education
We reimburse participation in relevant conferences and courses, and regularly conduct internal bootcamps. We also provide access to discounted English language courses.
Entertainment and merch
Every year we hold hundreds of events around the world, including contests, sports challenges, parties, hackathons, and offline events for individual teams.
Fitness
We support leading a healthy lifestyle and offer reimbursement for gym memberships, or fitness app subscriptions.
Community involvement
We launch charity projects and support the initiatives of employees through our grant competition.
Work Format
Remote or from one of the company's offices.
Please be aware that all correspondence with representatives of our company is conducted via “playrix.com” exclusively and no other entities.
